<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Mess Hall</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Neelix is pouring an orange drink.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Anthraxic citrus peel, orange juice with just a hint of papalla seed extract. An experimental blend.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>TUVOK:  The success rate of your culinary experiments has not been high.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Ensign Golwat tried some yesterday, and she thought it was delicious. In fact, she had a second glass, and she never has seconds.</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Ensign Golwat is Bolian. Her tongue has a cartilaginous lining. It would protect her against even the most corrosive acid.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>NEELIX:  All I ask is that you try it, Mister Vulcan.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok sniffs and sips.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Impressive.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Ah! I'll start squeezing that second glass. Breakfast is coming right up. Porakan eggs.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Porakan?</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>NEELIX:  The most flavourful eggs in the sector. Scrambled with a little dill weed, a touch of rengazo, a galactic favourite. Now, these eggs were not easy to prepare. After we picked them up on Porakas Four, I had to sterilise them in a cryostatic chamber for three days. Then each and every one had to be parboiled</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Mister Neelix, I would prefer not to hear the life history of my breakfast.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>NEELIX:  On Talax it's a tradition to share the history of a meal before you begin eating. It's a way of enhancing the culinary experience. My mother was brilliant. She could make every course, every garnish come alive by making it a character in a story. My favourite was the one about the crustacean who</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Flames surge up around the egg pan, setting the contents alight. Neelix quickly smothers it with a lid.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>TUVOK:  What happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Er, some sort of power overload. I'm afraid it decimated your breakfast. This is what my mother would call a tragic ending.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Engineering has been making adjustments to the plasma conduits to accommodate a new energy source. It may have created a thermal surge in the galley systems.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>JANEWAY [OC]:  Janeway to Tuvok. Please report to the bridge. Mister Neelix, I'd like you to join us as well.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Aye, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 50126.4. We have detected a gaseous anomaly that contains sirillium, a highly combustible and versatile energy source. We've altered course to investigate.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Sirillium?</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Yes, and possibly large amounts of it. If so, we're going to need to stockpile as much as we can. I'd like to convert storage bay three into a containment chamber.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>NEELIX:  My pantry.</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I'm sorry, Neelix. You're going to have to make other arrangements.</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Of course, Captain. You know, if I injected sirillium into my thermal array, it might improve cooking time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>TORRES:  Yes, and blow up half your kitchen in the process. Sirillium is far more useful as a warp plasma catalyst.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>TUVOK:  The gas can also be used to boost deflector shield efficiency.</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  The vultures are circling.</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Well, there's certainly no shortage of good ideas. Have all department heads submit proposals for sirillium usage.</td></tr>

