<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A girl is hanging over a big drop. A young Tuvok is trying to save her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>GIRL:  Help me, Tuvok! Please don't let go! Tuvok! Don't let me fall!</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok staggers along the corridor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>GIRL:  No!</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Her fingers slip from young Tuvok's grasp and she falls.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok enters and collapses, eyes staring. Later, Janeway is present while the EMH scans Tuvok.</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I was holding a young girl by the hand, tying to prevent her from falling from a precipice. I was unable to keep my grip, and she fell to her death. And there is more. I had an emotional response anxiety, fear. An almost irrational anger at myself for letting her fall.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>KES:  When did that happen?</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>TUVOK:  It never happened. The girl was unfamiliar, and I've never been in that situation. It was me as a child, and it did seem like a memory, but I don't recall the incident.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>EMH:  Well, it was definitely a traumatic episode. Your heart rate accelerated to three hundred beats per minute. Your adrenaline levels rose by one hundred thirteen percent and your neuroelectrical readings nearly jumped off the scale. If you were human, I'd say you had a severe panic attack.</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I am not human.</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>EMH:  No kidding. I don't know what happened to you, but there can be any number of explanations. Hallucination, telepathic communication from another race, repressed memory, momentary contact with a parallel reality. Take your pick. The universe is such a strange place.</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I'll have Mister Kim examine the sensor logs. Maybe our proximity to the nebula is affecting you somehow.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>EMH:  In the meantime, Lieutenant, you are free to go. All of your vital signs have returned to normal, and I don't see any residual systemic damage. But I want you to wear this neurocortical monitor. In case you have another episode, it'll record a complete encephalographic profile and alert sickbay at the same time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The EMH places the device behind Tuvok's left ear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>TUVOK:  A wise precaution, Doctor. Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Tuvok's quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok has lit candles and is using bizarre building blocks.</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Structure, logic, function, control. A structure cannot stand without a foundation. Logic is the foundation of function. Function is the essence of control. I am in control. I am in control.</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: But the house of not-cards collapses, then the doorbell chimes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Enter. Kes. What is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>KES:  The doctor wanted me to adjust your neurocortical monitor to pick up additional peptide readings. I can come back later if this is a bad time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L67"><td><a href="#L67">67</a></td><td>TUVOK:  No. You may proceed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L68"><td><a href="#L68">68</a></td><td>KES:  What are you working on?</td></tr>

<tr id="L69"><td><a href="#L69">69</a></td><td>TUVOK:  It is called a keethara.</td></tr>

<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>KES:  Keethara. What does that mean?</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>TUVOK:  The approximate translation is structure of harmony. It is used as a meditational aid. Building it requires precise balance and spatial acuity. It helps to focus thought and refine mental control.</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>KES:  At the moment, it doesn't look very harmonious.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>TUVOK:  No, it does not.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>KES:  I'm curious. What does a keethara look like when it's done?</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>TUVOK:  The form is not predefined. It is a reflection of the builder's state of mind. Thus, it is different each time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>KES:  I'd like to see it when it's finished. Well, good night.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Kes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>KES:  It's all right. I understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kes leaves.</td></tr>

<tr id="L80"><td><a href="#L80">80</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Structure, logic, function, control. A structure cannot stand without a foundation. Logic is the foundation of function. Function is the essence of control. I am in control. I am in control.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Corridor</td></tr>
<tr id="L81"><td><a href="#L81">81</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  So how are you feeling this morning?</td></tr>

<tr id="L82"><td><a href="#L82">82</a></td><td>TUVOK:  If you are referring to yesterday's incident, I haven't experienced any further problems. I am fit for duty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L83"><td><a href="#L83">83</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  I didn't ask because I'm concerned about your ability to perform, I'm concerned about you.</td></tr>

