<tr id="L93"><td><a href="#L93">93</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I suggest we conduct a tachyon sweep of the nebula. It would reveal the presence of any cloaked ships.</td></tr>

<tr id="L94"><td><a href="#L94">94</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  Cloaked ships?</td></tr>

<tr id="L95"><td><a href="#L95">95</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Yes. We should be extremely cautious this close to Klingon space.</td></tr>

<tr id="L96"><td><a href="#L96">96</a></td><td>TORRES:  Tuvok, the Klingon Empire is on the other side of the galaxy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L97"><td><a href="#L97">97</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Yes. Yes, you are right, of course. I'm uncertain why I would make such an obvious error.</td></tr>

<tr id="L98"><td><a href="#L98">98</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  Maybe you should go back to Sickbay. Tuvok?</td></tr>

<tr id="L99"><td><a href="#L99">99</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is back at the cliff.</td></tr>

<tr id="L100"><td><a href="#L100">100</a></td><td>GIRL [memory]:  Help me, Tuvok! Please don't let go! No!</td></tr>

<tr id="L101"><td><a href="#L101">101</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Chakotay catches Tuvok as he falls. The neurocortical monitor is going crazy.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L102"><td><a href="#L102">102</a></td><td>EMH:  I think we may be dealing with a repressed memory. The memory engrams in the dorsal region of the hippocampus are being disrupted. It's causing physical damage to the surrounding tissue. In Vulcan medicine, this is known as t'lokan schism. It means that the subject is inhibiting a traumatic memory, which is beginning to resurface.</td></tr>

<tr id="L103"><td><a href="#L103">103</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  And that's causing brain damage?</td></tr>

<tr id="L104"><td><a href="#L104">104</a></td><td>EMH:  Strange, I know. In human subjects, repressed memories are nothing more than psychological traumas which can be dealt with, with standard therapeutic techniques. But in Vulcans, there is a physical reaction to the battle between the conscious and the unconscious. In extreme cases, the mind of the patient can literally lobotomise itself.</td></tr>

<tr id="L105"><td><a href="#L105">105</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  What's the treatment?</td></tr>

<tr id="L106"><td><a href="#L106">106</a></td><td>EMH:  There is no medical treatment for this condition. Vulcan psychocognitive research suggests that the patient initiate a mind-meld with a family member, and the two of them attempt to bring the repressed memory into the conscious mind.</td></tr>

<tr id="L107"><td><a href="#L107">107</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I'm the closest thing Tuvok has to a family member on this ship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L108"><td><a href="#L108">108</a></td><td>EMH:  That's why I've asked you to come. He has a request to make of you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L109"><td><a href="#L109">109</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is on a biobed, meditating.</td></tr>

<tr id="L110"><td><a href="#L110">110</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Did the doctor explain the situation to you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L111"><td><a href="#L111">111</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Yes. Tuvok, are you sure it's the right thing to do?</td></tr>

<tr id="L112"><td><a href="#L112">112</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I don't know how else to proceed. The doctor tells me that this is a memory. And yet, no matter how hard I try, I cannot remember. If the doctor is correct, if this is an experience I pushed into my unconscious mind, it could be very dangerous to me, even life-threatening. I realise it's asking a great deal of you, Captain, and I did consider turning to one of the Vulcans on the ship, but this meld would be more intimate than most. A family member is normally chosen because of the implicit trust that usually exists. On this ship, I trust you more than anyone else.</td></tr>

<tr id="L113"><td><a href="#L113">113</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Whatever happens, I'll be there for you, Tuvok. I'll help you get through this.</td></tr>

<tr id="L114"><td><a href="#L114">114</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I will initiate the meld and attempt to access the memory fragment. Once that has been accomplished, you will act as my pyllora.</td></tr>

<tr id="L115"><td><a href="#L115">115</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Your pyllora?</td></tr>

<tr id="L116"><td><a href="#L116">116</a></td><td>TUVOK:  My guide, my counsellor. You will help me reconstruct the memory in its entirety. And as I am reliving it, you will help me to objectify the experience. By processing the experience, rather than repressing it, I can begin to overcome my fear, anger and the other emotional responses, and to reintegrate the memory into my conscious mind.</td></tr>

<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  When I'm in your memory, will I actually be reliving it with you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>TUVOK:  No. I will be the only one who notices your presence. You will be an observer in the memory, but not a participant. This will give you the freedom to guide me objectively.</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  When do we start?</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I will need time to prepare. Please return in one hour.</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: One hour later, Tuvok and Janeway are sitting opposite each other in chairs, in the surgery bay. Janeway is also wearing a monitor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>EMH:  We're ready when you are, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Your mind to my mind. Your thoughts to my thoughts. I am taking us back, back to the boy that I was, the boy lying on the precipice.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Excelsior bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Under attack. The crew are wearing 23rd century Federation uniforms. Welcome to the [1]Undiscovered Country.</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>SULU:  Return fire!</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>VALTANE:  They've knocked out our targeting scanners.</td></tr>

